The University’s administrative search process is complex, involving search firms, search committees, applications and multiple rounds of interviews.
‘Big picture sense’: The beginnings of a searchAt the heart of every administrative search is a search committee, typically consisting of 10 to 20 people drawn from Duke’s supply of Trustees, deans, faculty, administrators and students.
Bovender said that after all applications were received, the presidential search committee conducted a forced ranking in which committee members were required to rank each applicant.
This is also when the search committee calls references for the candidates, Nowicki said.
Certain roles have recently trended more toward internal or external candidates, Nowicki explained.